General Assembly Substitute Bill No. 336
February Session, 2026
AN ACT CONCERNING A STUDY OF HOUSING POLICY.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 Section 1. (Effective from passage) The Department of Housing shall
2 conduct a study on the housing policies of the state. Such study shall
3 examine each housing program, the policy it was designed to address
4 and the effectiveness of such program. Not later than January 1, 2027,
5 the Commissioner of Housing shall report, in accordance with the
6 provisions of section 11-4a of the general statutes, to the joint standing
7 committee of the General Assembly having cognizance of matters
8 relating to housing.
This act shall take effect as follows and shall amend the following
sections:
Section 1 from passage New section
Statement of Legislative Commissioners:
The title was changed.
HSG Joint Favorable Subst. -LCO
